31/10/2002
TIRANA, Albania -- Arben Malaj, Albanian Minister of Economy and Raffaele Fitto, President of Italy's Puglia region, signed an economic co-operation agreement in Tirana on Wednesday (30 October). 
Fitto said the agreement aims to consolidate relations between Puglia and the Albanian government, mainly in the sectors of infrastructure, environment and tourism. 
In addition to the planned bilateral projects, he said, regional initiatives would be implemented. 
(ATA - 30/10/02)
